This is how basketball changes lives.

I remember the one in early 2000s with AI, Marbury, j kidd, Kobe, kg, and the rest going at it to one or even two overtimes. I don't think anybody got injured in that game. But it was better than last night's game because nothing had to be changed, the game was intense from the first quarter. I put all the blame on the players for the last 5 yrs of shitty Allstar games. They're the ones who make the ultimate decision. They got soft and worried about injuries but there are ways to play hard, play defense and play safe. I would've hated to pay the for the ticket to the all star games in the last 5 or so yrs. I hated watching the highlights the game had turned into suck a joke. It's been embarrassing for the players if you ask me and finally they woke up
